theorem Topology.closure_interior_union_subset_union_closure_interior
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    closure (interior (A ∪ B)) ⊆ closure (interior A) ∪ closure (interior B) := by
  -- Step 1: relate the interiors.
  have h_int :
      interior (A ∪ B) ⊆ interior A ∪ interior B :=
    Topology.interior_union_subset (X := X) (A := A) (B := B)
  -- Step 2: take closures, preserving the inclusion.
  have h_cl :
      closure (interior (A ∪ B)) ⊆ closure (interior A ∪ interior B) :=
    closure_mono h_int
  -- Step 3: rewrite the right–hand side using an existing equality.
  have h_eq :
      closure (interior A ∪ interior B) =
        closure (interior A) ∪ closure (interior B) :=
    Topology.closure_union_interior_eq_union_closure_interior
      (X := X) (A := A) (B := B)
  -- Step 4: combine the two facts.
  simpa [h_eq] using h_cl
